# Communication — Commits + PRs

Use conventional commits and clean PR descriptions.

- Commit format: `type(scope): description`
- Types: feat, fix, chore, refactor, docs, test, style, perf
- One commit per logical change (not one giant commit)
- Reference issues: `Closes #123`, `Related to #456`
- Pull request descriptions: what, why, how, testing done
- Document breaking changes with `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer
- Keep commit messages under 72 characters for the subject line
